A SUSPECT wanted for murder and his two accomplices died in
a gun battle with cops. The suspect who was wanted for murder and his two suspected
accomplices were fatally wounded after they started a gun battle with police
along the R612 road in Umzinto North yesterday. The KZN cops spokesman Colonel Robert Netshiunda said police
had operationalised intelligence information and cornered the suspects as they
were leaving a mall in Scottburgh. "The police ordered the suspects to stop but the trio
defied the lawful instructions and sped off. A high-speed chase ensued with
police continuing efforts to pull them over," he said. You must be SIGNED IN to comment! He said with police closing in on them, the suspects fired
shots at the men of law and a shootout ensued. "After the gunfire three suspects were found to have
sustained fatal gunshot wounds. No police officer was reported injured,"
he said. Colonel Netshiunda said the deceased are linked to a murder
that they allegedly committed in Dududu in October 2022.